caption: They are so kind and make the best bubble tea

I usually order online and on occasion I go on, but today I went in and the lady that was working there this afternoon was really rude and it took forever for my order. Everyone else is usually nice but she was real snappy. And it wasn't just me that she was being rude to, another customer was waiting for her drink as long as me, and I was waiting for about 15 minutes. The customer had politely asked her how much longer for the drink, and the worker snapped at her &told her that she needed to wait and she'll let her know when it was ready.

Came in with a friend ( we are both black)to order and there were no other customers inside. As we tried to order the person at the register with a ponytail rudely told us we would have to order at the kiosk if we were paying with a card. We were very confused because it was not like they were busy or making drinks. The kiosk is clearly a high touch surface and I doubt it had been wiped down recently. It was our first time ordering at the kiosk and we were struggling so we asked a question and the person responded that we would have to use the app on our phones instead to order. At first I thought it was just because the person taking the order was rude but now it seems like there might of been an alternative reason. Two white people walked in and the person at the counter gladly took their order. They not only each ordered food but also drinks (a much bigger order than ours as we only ordered a drink each). The person had no problem that they were paying with a card. I don’t know what type of establishment this is but you need to train your employees about discrimination. This was extremely disappointing and unacceptable.

There was only 1 employee here but he worked efficiently! I do wish that he had another employee there because after ringing people up, he had to quickly rinse his hands then make the drinks which isn’t sanitary at all but I understand not wanted to wash your hands every 30 seconds because it’s extremely drying but at least put on gloves. Im still giving 5 stars because he was very kind and knowledgeable about the drinks and my drink was delicious!
